Drill 3 — Hierarchical Variance Tree: Entity -> BU -> LOB
Exact task statement
Explain the latest closed month variance versus prior month using the hierarchy Entity to BU to LOB.
Build order
9.	Identify latest_closed_month and prior_month.
10.	Aggregate revenue by entity, bu, lob for both months. 
11.	Join current and prior values.
12.	Compute variance amount, variance percent, contribution to total variance, and variance rank.
Validation checks
•	Sum of variance_amt across all rows must equal company month-on-month variance.
•	Rank by absolute variance, not signed variance.
•	Handle zero prior-month revenue consistently.
Final output template
entity	bu	lob	current_month_revenue	prior_month_revenue	variance_amt	variance_pct	contribution_to_total_variance_pct	variance_rank	variance_direction
UAE	Ocean BU	Ocean	23300000	21900000	1400000	6.4%	32.6%	1	Increase
Output column definitions
•	variance_amt = current_month_revenue - prior_month_revenue.
•	variance_pct = variance_amt / prior_month_revenue.
•	contribution_to_total_variance_pct = variance_amt / total company variance.
--=====================================================================================
SOLUTION:
--=====================================================================================
  With cte_1 as(
Select 
	rev_mth_dt,
	entity,
	bu,
	lob,
	Sum(total_revenue) as total_revenue,
	Max(rev_mth_dt) over() curr_mth,
	date_trunc('month', (Max(rev_mth_dt) over() - 1)::date)::date prior_mth
From platinum.segment_month_base
Group by
	rev_mth_dt,
	entity,
	bu,
	lob
Order by rev_mth_dt desc
),
cte_2 as(
Select 
	*,
	Sum(total_revenue) curr_mth_rev,
	entity || bu || lob as unique_key
From cte_1
Where
rev_mth_dt = curr_mth
Group by
	rev_mth_dt,
	entity,
	bu,
	lob,
	total_revenue,
	curr_mth,
	prior_mth
),
cte_3 as
(Select 
	*,
	Sum(total_revenue) prior_mth_rev,
	entity || bu || lob as unique_key
From cte_1
where rev_mth_dt = prior_mth
Group by
	rev_mth_dt,
	entity,
	bu,
	lob,
	total_revenue,
	curr_mth,
	prior_mth
)
Select
	c2.entity,
	c2.bu,
	c2.lob,
	coalesce(c2.curr_mth_rev,0) curr_mth_rev,
	coalesce(c3.prior_mth_rev,0) prior_mth_rev,
	coalesce((c2.curr_mth_rev - c3.prior_mth_rev),0) as variance_amt,
	Round((coalesce((c2.curr_mth_rev - c3.prior_mth_rev),0) / nullif(c3.prior_mth_rev,0))::numeric,2) as var_pct,
	ROUND(
    	(COALESCE(c2.curr_mth_rev - c3.prior_mth_rev, 0)
        /
        NULLIF(SUM(c2.curr_mth_rev) OVER () - SUM(c3.prior_mth_rev) OVER (),0))::numeric,2) contri_to_total_var,
	Row_Number() over(order by abs(coalesce((c2.curr_mth_rev - c3.prior_mth_rev),0)) desc) variance_rank
From cte_2 c2
Left Join cte_3 c3
On c2.unique_key = c3.unique_key
Group by
	c2.entity,
	c2.bu,
	c2.lob,
	c2.curr_mth_rev,
	c3.prior_mth_rev
